{
  "texts": [
    "The boundary interval I ′ is defined similarly.",
    "Moreover, I can be glued to I ′ to obtain a new surface homeomorphic to Σ D as extended surfaces.",
    "We will identify the glued surface with Σ D. Denote by gl: A(Σ C ⊔ Σ C ′) ≃ A(Σ C) ⊗ A(Σ C ′) → A(Σ D) the associated gluing map as described in Section 3.3: The claim follows by noting that |F D | -|F C | -|F C ′ | = |I in | and that gl also imposes compatible boundary conditions δ b I,b ′ I ′.",
    "□ 5 Anyon States 5.1 Unique anyon states from local constraints Let C be an infinite region such that Σ C is homeomorphic to R 2 with an open disk removed.",
    "The associated surface Σ C has a single connected boundary component S. We denote the corresponding Tube S action by t = t S for the remainder of this section."
  ]
}